    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Venus</h2>
        <p>Venus is often referred to as Earth's twin because of its similar size and structure, but it has a very thick and toxic atmosphere.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Earth</h2>
        <p>Earth is the only known planet to support life. It has a balanced atmosphere and vast oceans.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Mars</h2>
        <p>Mars is known as the Red Planet because of its reddish appearance, caused by iron oxide on its surface.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Jupiter</h2>
        <p>Jupiter is the largest planet in the solar system. It has a giant storm called the Great Red Spot and many moons.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Saturn</h2>
        <p>Saturn is famous for its stunning rings, made of ice and rock particles. It's the second-largest planet in the solar system.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Uranus</h2>
        <p>Uranus is unique because it rotates on its side. It has a blue-green color due to the methane in its atmosphere.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="planet">
        <h2>Neptune</h2>
        <p>Neptune is the farthest planet from the Sun and has a deep blue color due to its methane-rich atmosphere.</p>
    </div>
</section>

